The paper deals with the problem of domain adaptation for semantic segmentation, which is a task in computer vision (CV). The proposed method involves learning discriminative feature representations and using an adversarial learning scheme, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). The paper also mentions the use of label histograms, which is a technique used in natural language processing (CL). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (MM) research.
